<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mongolian PM Meets Chinese Deputy PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Mongolian Prime Minister
Mendsaikhan Enkhsaikhan and visiting Chinese Vice-Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen said here today that the two
countries will further develop their friendship and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
China and Mongolia, which share a border of more than 4,000
kilometers, have made great progress in their relationships in
various fields through common efforts, said Qian during the
meeting with Enkhsaikhan.
</P>
<P>
The two countries are economically complementary and have the
potential and conditions for further expanding economic and trade
cooperation, said Qian, who arrived here today for a four-day
official visit.
</P>
<P>
China attaches great importance to trade and economic relations
with Mongolia and will make efforts to expand inter-governmental
cooperation between the two countries in trade and economy and to
encourage mutual investment and the cooperation between the
businesses of the two countries, said Qian.
</P>
<P>
Enkhsaikhan told Qian that the Mongolian government will boost
the long-term friendship and cooperation with China in the spirit
of the treaty of friendship and cooperation between China and
Mongolia signed in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Enkhsaikhan hoped that the Sino-Mongolian relationship will be
brought to a new height during the five-year term of his
government, which was formed in June, 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
