<HEADLINE> Bomb Explodes in Athens Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Initial reports said the blast took place at 15:30 local time
(13:30 GMT) in the office of Greece's former Public Order Minister
Stelios Papathemelis.
</P>
<P>
The reports said people in the building were evacuated before
the explosion, following an anonymous call to the local police
that a bomb was planted there by an organization called
"Revolutionary Nuclei."
</P>
<P>
In a separate blast here today, a car from the Austrian embassy
was seriously damaged by a fire-bomb, which was thrown by two
unidentified persons.
</P>
<P>
Police are investigating the two incidents. 
</P>
