<HEADLINE> U.S. Airman Disappears in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 19 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. airman has been missing on
the Greek island of Crete since August 12, a press official of the
U.S. embassy here said today.
</P>
<P>
The official said that Larry Gonzales, a satellite
communications expert, disappeared after returning from work at
the Souda base on the island to his hotel in Akrotiri.
</P>
<P>
The embassy refused to comment on the nature of Gonzales' duty
at the U.S. base of Souda. The local press said Gonzales'
responsibility is to analyze satellite messages.
</P>
<P>
Greek police and U.S. secret services launched a 24-hour search
after the missing report but found nothing.
</P>
<P>
Two days later, police found Gonzales' car, a mini Cooper,
abandoned a few yards from his hotel.
</P>
<P>
FBI agents were reportedly due in Crete in the next few days to
join the search and investigations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
