<HEADLINE> France Commemorates Paris Police Uprising against Nazis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The French government today
commemorated the 53rd anniversary of the uprising of Paris police
against German Nazi occupiers.
</P>
<P>
French Interior Minister Jean-Pierre Chevenement said at a
ceremony marking the event that French police force is now
"confronted with great challenges" to defend the values of the
French republic and democracy.
</P>
<P>
"The national police, especially the Parisian police, finds
itself faced with the great challenges generated by the economic
and social difficulties and by the crisis of certain values which
make up our republic," said Chevenement.
</P>
<P>
He said that one of the priorities of police is to fight crimes
to "contribute to the maintenance of social cohesion."
</P>
<P>
He also said that violence in French high schools makes up a
big problem which he is "resolutely engaged" in fighting.
</P>
</TEXT>
