<HEADLINE> Foot, Mouth Cattle Disease Breaks Out in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's Lands and Agriculture
Minister Kumbirai Kangai today said an outbreak of the foot and
mouth cattle disease has broken out in Bikita and Chiredzi
districts of Masvingo province in south Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
The minister told the congress of the Zimbabwe Farmers Union
that affected areas were far away from European Union beef
catchment areas.
</P>
<P>
He said teams from the Veterinary Services Department have
been deployed to the districts to vaccinate affected cattle while
more tests are being carried out to curb the spread of the
disease.
</P>
<P>
The outbreak of the contagious viral cattle disease which can
cause instant deaths in cattle was discovered last week.
</P>
<P>
He said, "the cattle in the area have been quarantined and
road blocks have been set up to avoid the disease's spread to
other areas."
</P>
<P>
"Fortunately, the affected areas are more than 300 km away
from the European Union beef catchment areas, so our exports will
continue," he said.
</P>
<P>
Last time that foot and mouth affected beef exports from
Zimbabwe was between 1989 and 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
