<HEADLINE> Namibia to Build Hydro-electric Dam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The building of a
hydro-electricity dam on the Cunene River in Namibia was both
technically and financially viable, Namibian President Sam Nujoma
said today.
</P>
<P>
Sources reaching here today quoted Nujoma as saying that an
in-depth engineering, financial and environment study was
expected to be completed by October.
</P>
<P>
Nujoma said that his government would not be deterred by the
misguided activities of those who want to impede the national
economic development and the upliftment of the standards of
people.
</P>
<P>
Nujoma's remarks was apparently referring to Namibia's
Ovahimba people, who have threatened to take legal action if the
government went ahead with the dam-building scheme.
</P>
<P>
The Ovahimba's ancestral sites and grazing land reportedly
would be flooded if the dam was built on the Cunene River.
</P>
<P>
Ovahimba's Chief Hikuminue Kapika warned recently if the dam
was built, "we will all gather there and they have to build the
dam on top of us".  
</P>
