<HEADLINE> Jordanian King Calls on US to Continue Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, August 19 (Xinhua) - King Hussein of Jordan today
called on the U.S. to continue its effort for Mideast peace in
order to achieve a just and comprehensive peace in the region.
</P>
<P>
Hussein made the remark while meeting a U.S. congressional
delegation, Radio Jordan reported.
</P>
<P>
The king stressed the need to resume and intensify the efforts
to push forward the Israeli-Palestinian peace negotiations which
have been stalled since Israel began construction of a Jewish
settlement in East Jerusalem in March.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized the necessity to overcome the crisis after the
double suicide bombings on July 30 in West Jerusalem which killed
16 people and wounded 170 others.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. delegation praised the king for his efforts to
achieve peace in the region and underlined the U.S. government's
efforts to help Jordan develop its economy in various fields.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, which arrived here Monday on a two-day official
visit, also met Jordanian Prime minister Abdul-Salam Majali and
Minister of Foreign Affairs Fayez Tarawneh before its meeting with
Hussein.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. government has decided to grant Jordan with 300
million U.S. dollars worth of military aid and 100 million
dollars worth of economic aid to help enhance its role in the
peace process and develop its economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
