<HEADLINE> Germany's Bayer Group First-Half Profits Up 13 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Germany's third biggest chemicals
maker Bayer today said its first-half profits surged 13 percent to
1.7 billion marks (926 million U.S. dollars), and expected that
the group's annual turnover would top 50 billion marks this year.
</P>
<P>
The group based in Leverkusen north of Cologne achieved 27.4
billion mark sales during the period, up 11 percent, thanks to
increased business in America and eastern Europe.
</P>
<P>
Bayer said it was "confident" sales for the full year of 1997
would exceed 50 million marks, expecting continued rising demand
and stability of exchange rates.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the group boosted its sales to 48.6 billion marks
and pre-tax earnings to 4.5 billion marks.  
</P>
