<DOCNO> XIE19970820.0051 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ECOMOG Adjusts Deployment in Liberia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The West African Peace-keeping
Force known as ECOMOG is to adjust its deployment in Liberia to
ensure the national security of that country.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here today quoted ECOMOG commander,
major-general Victor Malu as saying this at the weekend at the
ECOMOG headquarters in Monrovia, during a visit by Kalu Kaluniya,
the out-going U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees' resident
representative in Liberia.
</P>
<P>
The commander said that the re-deployment will fortify
Liberia's border with its neighbouring countries, especially with
Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that the trouble in Sierra Leone triggered off
by a military takeover on May 25 is having an adverse effect on
the security situation in Liberia, which has just stepped out a
seven-year bloody civil war.
</P>
<P>
Fierce fightings in Sierra Leone have reportedly driven a
large number of refugees, including about 200 disarmed militiamen
into Liberia.
</P>
<P>
Malu also took the chance to call on the Sierra Leonean
military government to accept an international request to restore
ousted President Ahmed Kabbah, adding that his troops are ready
and capable of enforcing a reverse of the situation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
