<HEADLINE> World University Games Open in Sicily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PALERMO, Sicily, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The 19th World Universiade
were officially opened here on Tuesday evening with a record entry of
some 6,000 athletes from more than 170 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The games, second largest sports meet only after Olympics, will
start a new era as for the first time the games will be held in
three cities of Palermo, Catania and Messina.
</P>
<P>
The 19th World Universiade will feature in 10 sports of
swimming, diving, water polo, gymnastics, tennis, football, fencing,
basketball, volleyball and athletics. The football tournament has
already begun on Monday with eight group matches being played.
</P>
<P>
The games will also attract some world class athletes including
double Olympic swimming gold medalist Penny Heynes of South Africa,
newly-crowned walking world champion Annarita Sidoti of Italy and
several other Olympic medalists and world champions.
</P>
<P>
Primo Nebiolo, president of FISU, said that the meet is a chance
for Sicilian people to show their hospitality to the world and at
the same time, a challenge to the organizing committee to show their
organizing skills.
</P>
<P>
The organizing committee will have a tough task of making the
games a great success, especially as the games are being held in
three cities 100 to 200 kilometers away from each other.
</P>
<P>
Besides transportation, which bothered the organizers of the
Atlanta Olympic Games, the Universiade organizers will also cope with
the problems of computer system, communication and so on.
</P>
<P>
The games will end on August 31. 
</P>
</TEXT>
