<HEADLINE> China Should Expand Mineral Resources Development: Minister (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding China's geological prospecting work since the time of
the 14th National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC),
in 1992, Song said the country had scored "remarkable progress,"
and the country's development of mineral resources had gradually
been brought onto a course featuring "sustainable development of
resources and the environment."
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that so far, China has found mineral resources
in more than 25,000 places. Since 1992, mineral resources have
been located on over 1,000 of these sites.
</P>
<P>
China has become one of the several mining countries in the
world to have a complete variety of mineral resources and rich
reserves.
</P>
<P>
In terms of gross volume, China ranks high in the area of
verified mineral reserves, mining of mineral ore and the
consumption of mineral products. Geological prospecting and mining
has supported the operation of 70 percent of China's national
economic departments, with mining alone providing Chinese people
with more than 14 million job opportunities.
</P>
<P>
The annual mining volume of mineral ore in China amounts to 5.8
billion tons. China ranks the first worldwide for the output of
coal, iron and steel, and cement, and is also a global leader in
the output of non-ferrous metals, petroleum and mineral products
for chemical industrial production.
</P>
<P>
After years of effort, "China has established a strong supply
mechanism of energy, raw materials and mineral commodities," Song
said, adding that this has made "tremendous contributions" to the
country's modernization drive.
</P>
</TEXT>
