<HEADLINE> Steel Plant's Extension Project Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The Extension Project of the
Panzhihua Iron and Steel (Group) Company in southwest China's
Sichuan Province, which has been completed, is set to increase the
company's steel production capacity to three million tons annually.
</P>
<P>
General Manager Hong Jibi today told a group of Beijing-based
reporters at a press conference that the completion of the project
has changed the layout of the country's iron and steel industry
and speeded up the exploration of local mineral resources,
including a nearly 10-billion-ton reserve of iron ore in Sichuan's
Panzhihua-Xichang area.
</P>
<P>
Hong said the first phase of the iron and steel complex was
built from 1965-74, and had an annual capacity of 1.5 million
tons. And the second-phase extension project, was launched in 1986
and cost about nine billion yuan. The complex is now capable of
producing both hot-rolled and cold-rolled steel plates.
</P>
<P>
Hong said his company has paid back 210 million US dollars of
overseas loans, and that it is the first industrial enterprise in
China that has raised funds from the international financial
market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
