<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Musicians from Beijing, Paris,
Berlin, Moscow, Hanoi, Brussels, Cologne and Vienna will gather in
the Chinese capital to mark the International Sister Cities Music
Week which runs from September 1-7.
</P>
<P>
The 40-plus foreign musicians participating in the activities
will play the classic pieces from their homelands mixed with some
modern variations. Many of the performers have received awards in
international competitions.
</P>
