<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1530 GMT, August 20 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN -- An overnight house fire in the northern German town of
Rheine killed seven people, including four children, and seriously
injured two others, the local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
The deaths were likely to be all members of an ethnic-German
family which migrated to Germany from the former Soviet Union five
years ago, police said.
</P>
<P>
The two injured had eventually managed to escape the fire by
jumping from a second-floor window to a mattress which
firefighters had dragged before the house from a nearby bed shop.
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- China today expressed deepest regret for the open
support given by some senior Japanese officials to the recent
statement by Japan's Chief Cabinet Secretary Seiroku Kajiyama
concerning the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Kajiyama clearly indicated in a recent statement that the scope
of the Japan-US security cooperation should include the Taiwan
Straits.
</P>
<P>
Japan's deputy chief cabinet secretary claimed today that the
remarks of Kajiyama reflect the position of the Japanese
government and there is nothing wrong with that. He noted that
some other officials of the Japanese government also supports this
view. 
</P>
