<HEADLINE> HK's PLC Adopts Motion on Vietnamese Boat People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The Provisional Legislative
Council (PLC), the legislative arm of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR), today adopted a motion on Vietnamese
boat people.
</P>
<P>
The motion, presented by Legislator Mrs. Selina Chow, urges the
 Hong Kong SAR government to repatriate as soon as possible all
Vietnamese boat people and illegal immigrants stranded in Hong
Kong, abolish the first asylum port policy, as well as recover
from the United Nations High Commission for Refugees the
1.1-billion-HK-dollar (141 million US dollars) advances made by
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The motion was passed with 26 voting for, 15 against and 2
abstentions, after being amended by Mr. Lau Kong-wah and Ms. Choy
So-yuk.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong became a first asylum port in 1979 when it was under
British rule. 
</P>
