<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada's Wholesale Trade Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Canada's wholesale trade slipped
0.8 percent in June to 17 billion U.S. dollars, following two
consecutive monthly increases, Statistics Canada said today.
</P>
<P>
However, overall sales in the first half of this year went up
by 11.8 percent from the same period in 1996, the federal
statistics agency noted.
</P>
<P>
In June, wholesalers reported weaker sales in 6 of the 11 trade
groups, mainly in the section of motor vehicles, farm machinery,
metals and food products.
</P>
<P>
As sales fell in June, Canada's inventories rose 1.2 percent
from the previous month to 24.2 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
"High inventories in conjunction with lower sales moved the
inventories-to-sales ratio to 1.42 in June compared with the
historic low of 1.40 recorded in May," the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Since 1981, the ratio "has been on a downward trend, which
partially reflects the `just-in-time shipments philosophy'
introduced in the 1980s."
</P>
<P>
The inventories-to-sales ratio normally peaks during a slowdown
of the economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970820.0099 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Coastal Areas Form Orderly Market System (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- China's eastern coastal areas
have set up a rational and orderly market set-up, after learning a
few lessons from the random growth of the market economy and
abandoning the concept of relying on their own regional economy,
People's Daily, China's leading newspaper, reported today.
</P>
<P>
The article cited Wenzhou, a coastal city in east China's
Zhejiang Province, as an example. The city began to develop its
industry in the late 1970s, when the reform and opening-up was
launched.
</P>
<P>
Hunting higher profits, many people in the city opened
factories to produce goods that were imitations of world-famous
brands, which undermined the reputation of the city's products.
</P>
<P>
With this in mind, the city worked out a strategy which focused
on quality control, and has greatly improved its commodity
production in the past four years.
</P>
<P>
Like Wenzhou, many areas in east China have attempted to smooth
out the disarray, meanwhile observing the law of market economy,
the article said.
</P>
<P>
A large group of enterprises known for a more refined sense of
quality and good reputation outlasted their competitors with poor
products and images, and developed into big group companies.
</P>
<P>
The south China island province of Hainan, the country's
largest special economic region, has drawn many international
investment companies by standardizing the economic cooperation,
promoting equal market competition and improving the efficiency of
the government organizations.
</P>
<P>
The city of Jinjiang in east China's Fujian Province has become
the most rapidly-developing place in the province thanks to the
focus on quality.
</P>
<P>
In addition, other parts of the market system, including stock,
information, technology and labor markets, have also undergone a
similar change from confusion to orderliness, according to the
article.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970820.0100 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Coastal Areas Form Orderly Market System (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The practice of following the traditional concept of regional
economy has been a bitter experience for many enterprises in coastal
areas.
</P>
<P>
In the "Silk Campaign" which was waged several years ago in
the silkworm-raising areas in east China, many Chinese silk
manufacturers reduced the prices of their products in the world
market to better compete. This led to major losses for a large
number of Chinese silk firms.
</P>
<P>
"Regional economy" refers to the economy, developed in the unit
of one county or city, which often leads to fierce competition
between various areas to obtain more energy, more raw material and
a larger share of the market, and the repeated construction of
primary industries.
</P>
<P>
As more people in east China became aware of the drawbacks of the
concept, they began to tear down the ideological walls between
regions and join the larger market economy.
</P>
<P>
The textile industry in Shaoxing, in east China's Zhejiang
Province, which took a pounding from the textile products from the
outside areas, introduced advanced techniques and turned out 220
million yuan (26.5 million US dollars) in revenue last year.
</P>
<P>
This shows, however, that though opening-up sometimes produced
growing pains in an area, it ultimately produced better economic
results, the article commented.
</P>
<P>
To gain investors' confidence, an area must improve its
economic environment, the article pointed out.
</P>
<P>
"The advantage of the city's future lies in the basic framework
of the socialist market economic system the city has just
established," said Li Youwei, the city party secretary of Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
In the past several years, Shenzhen has adopted more than 60
sets of local laws and regulations, 76 percent of which concern
the economy, and has formed a legal system for the special
economic region, which is mostly devoted to local commercial laws
and economic laws.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970820.0101 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Coastal Areas Form Orderly Market System (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The entire eastern coastal region has improved system of the
the socialist market economy by strengthening legislation in the
work.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the total number of economic cases which
occurred in the coastal areas amounted to two-thirds of the 1,265
cases sent by the local areas to the National People's Congress to
be filed during the 1993-1996 period.
</P>
<P>
Law should act as a "guardian" of the market economy, the
article said, and the government should take the responsibility of
executing the laws and practising macro-control on the market.
</P>
<P>
The city of Shishi in east China's Fujian Province eased its
control on local enterprises at the beginning of the reform and
opening-up, which led to a general disorderliness of the market.
</P>
<P>
The city then decided to readjust the policies on local
enterprises, providing guidances for the investors and uniting the
small enterprises to form a larger market.
</P>
<P>
The city has in this way cultivated some domestic famous brands
and became part of one of the 100 pilot counties in the country.
</P>
<P>
Illegal competition has become a major problem as the market
competition intensifies. More than 30,000 cases of monopolization
and illegal competition across the country have been investigated
in the last several years.
</P>
<P>
In coastal areas, bans have been put on the making of
imitations of famous brands, bribery in commercial activities,
false advertising, the leaking of commercial secrets and illegal
contests involving commercial goods, according to the article.
</P>
<P>
The preferential policies provide the coastal areas with
chances to develop earlier than other parts of the country, the
article said.
</P>
<P>
But as the standard socialist market economy is now taking
shape in these areas, the advantages of an improved market system
will gradually outweigh the preferential policies and geographic
advantages in their future development, the article said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970820.0102 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Supports Early Legislative Elections of Bosnian Serbs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 20 (Xinhua) -- France today expressed support to
early legislative elections in the Bosnian Serb sub-state of
Republika Srpska and withdrew its support for Bosnian Serb
president Biljana Plavsic.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse quoted French ambassador to Sarajevo, Yves
Gaudeul, as saying today in Banja Luka that France thinks the only
peaceful way out of the crisis in Republika Srpska is to organize
"free and democratic new legislative elections."
</P>
<P>
Plavsic Tuesday met with the United States envoy for former
Yugoslavia, Robert Gelhard, and the European Union High
Representative for Bosnia, Carlos Westerdorp, on the crisis in her
country.
</P>
<P>
Both envoys suggested that Bosnian Serbs hold early legislative
elections.
</P>
<P>
Bosnian Serbs held their last general elections in September
1996 in accordance with the Dayton peace agreement on Bosnia
signed in December 1995, which put an end to the 43-month civil
war in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
