<HEADLINE> EU Offers DPRK 6.175 Million ECUs in Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The European Union today
approved an aid program worth 6.175 million ECUs (6.65 million
U.S. dollars) to the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
The program, to be carried out by the EU's European Community
Humanitarian Office with the assistance of the Organization of
Medicine Without Borders, will be part of a nutrition program
launched by the United Nations Children's Fund.
</P>
<P>
It is also part of an EU food aid program worth 46.3 million
ECUs (49.8 million dollars). The program started in late May when
the 15-nation union decided to provide the DPRK with 155,000 tons
of food.
</P>
<P>
Flooding in 1995 and 1996 reportedly damaged the summer
harvests of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. The
U.N. Food and Agriculture Organization estimated last December
that the country needs to import at least 2.36 million tons of
food to make up the food shortage. 
</P>
