<HEADLINE> China to Host World Police Course of Higher Specialization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The 19th International Course of
Higher Specialization for Police Forces will open early next month
at the Beijing International Convention Center.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the course is the management of public security
and prevention of crimes. Participants can take part in in-depth
discussions on issues of the basics of public security management,
prevention of crimes, and international and domestic threats
facing police.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 senior police officers, experts and professors
from interior ministries and police forces of 50 countries and
regions throughout the world will participate in the talks. Some
international organizations will also send their delegates to the
week-long meeting from September 2-9.
</P>
<P>
The course, offered annually, is organized by the International
Center of Sociological, Panel and Penitentiary Research Studies
(INTERCENTER) which was founded in Italy in 1977.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Entao, honorable vice-chairman of the ICPO-INTERPOL, said
that China has sent a delegation of its senior police officers to
participate in the activities sponsored by the INTERCENTER every
year since 1982. The China Branch of the INTERCENTER was founded
in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Through such activities, the Chinese police forces have
expanded their cooperation and exchanges with countries around
the world in research studies for police, Zhu said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
