<HEADLINE> Senior CPC Official Meets Japanese Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, standing committee
member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC), met with a delegation from the
Japanese trade unions here today.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is here to participate in celebrations of the
25th anniversary of the normalization of diplomatic relations
between China and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
committee, said that in marking the anniversary, both China and
Japan should stick to the principles enshrined in the
Sino-Japanese Joint Declaration and the China-Japan Peace and
Friendship Treaty, bear in mind both positive and negative
historical experience, and treasure the hard-won Sino-Japanese
friendship.
</P>
<P>
Both countries should have their eyes on the overall situation
of Sino-Japanese friendship, remove all disturbances, and promote
the cause of friendship, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
He highly evaluated the great contribution made by the Japanese
trade unions in promoting the normalization of diplomatic
relations, and the development of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that both old and new friends from the
Japanese unions would increase their contacts with the All-China
Federation of Trade Unions (ACFTU) in order to deepen mutual
understanding, develop friendship, expand cooperation, and
contribute more to the Sino-Japanese friendship cause.
</P>
<P>
Daisaku Kohchiyama, vice-president of the Japanese Trade Union
Confederation, said that trade unions of China and Japan enjoy
traditional friendship, and they should further intensify their
communication as the 21st century is drawing near, with an effort
to push bilateral ties to a new stage.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is here at guest of the ACFTU. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
