<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Universities Enroll More Macao Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 20 (Xinhua) -- China's interior universities
recruited a total of 1,014 Macao students this year, a record
number following a steady increase over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the Macao Chinese Education Association said that
these students will go to 33 universities and colleges in the
coming September, which include such famous institutions of higher
learning as Beijing University and Qinghua University.
</P>
<P>
Over 700 freshmen will seek bachelor's degree after four years
of study, while 114 will seek master's degree and 11 will seek
doctor's degree at those institutions of higher learning.
</P>
<P>
Another 172 students will take preparatory courses at the
Ji'nan University in Guangdong province, the Overseas Chinese
University in Fujian province and Shantou University in Guangdong
for one year before becoming a formal college student.
</P>
<P>
The number of Macao students enrolled last year added up to
849, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
China's inland universities began recruiting Macao students in
the mid-1980s. The number rose continuously over the past several
years.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,942 Macao middle school graduates applied this
year, accounting for two-thirds of all graduates, according to the
sources. It means an increase of nearly 600 from the number of
last year's applicants.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that Macao students seemed most interested in such
majors as clinical medicine, biochemistry, mechanics and
electronics, construction and engineering, transportation,
administration, international trade, computer, education, law and
languages.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that the increasing enthusiasm for Chinese
universities among Macao graduates was largely because of the fact
 that China will resume its exercise of sovereignty over Macao as
of December 20, 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
