<HEADLINE> Japanese Embassy Aids Highway Construction in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The Japanese embassy in Beijing
has decided to donate 630,000 yuan for highway construction in
poverty-stricken Binxian county in northwest China's Shaanxi
Province.
</P>
<P>
The signing ceremony of the donation was held here today.
</P>
<P>
The donation will be used to build four bridges as part of the
construction of a 24.5 kilometer-long highway.
</P>
<P>
The highway, aimed at improving the local transport conditions,
is scheduled to be operational late this October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
