<HEADLINE> Ramos Clarifies Purpose of Meeting With Ranariddh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
today clarified that the purpose of his meeting Monday with
Cambodian Prince Norodom Ranariddh was to underscore the need for
peace to be restored in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
"We have no other interest than to hope for the best for
Cambodia and the people of Cambodia," Ramos said during his weekly
press conference in the Presidential Palace.
</P>
<P>
In his 40-minute meeting with Ranariddh, Ramos urged that all
political forces in Cambodia, including that of Ranariddh, be
allowed to participate in the general elections scheduled for next
year.
</P>
<P>
"We are just hoping to see peace starting with an agreement to
hold honest and orderly elections in Cambodia in May, 1998, that
is our primary effort," he said.
</P>
<P>
Ramos also said the membership of Cambodia in the Association
of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) is still a very strong
possibility, adding that the ASEAN thrust is for it to become a
family of 10 nations.
</P>
<P>
The President explained what he did in receiving Ranariddh was
also done by other ASEAN leaders.
</P>
<P>
"He has been making his rounds and we were not the first one he
has visited," the President said.
</P>
<P>
In his meeting with Ranariddh, Ramos also urged all warring
factions to restore peace, observe a ceasefire and end all acts of
war and violence "for the sake of innocent Cambodian people."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
