<HEADLINE> Quake Jolts Banda Aceh, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 4.6 on
the Richter scale today jolted Banda Aceh, capital of Aceh
Province, Indonesia, forcing thousands of people to stay outdoors.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake, which started at 2:20 p.m. and
lasted nearly one minute, was located west of Aceh, reports
reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The quake was also felt as far away as Lhoekseumawe, north
Aceh, the local office of the Meteorological and Geophysical
Agency said.
</P>
<P>
There was no immediate report on casualties and material
losses.
</P>
<P>
the quake is the first to hit the province this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
