<HEADLINE> Commentary: Tremendous Contributions of Deng Xiaoping's Theory (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- People's Daily and Xinhua News
Agency today jointly published a commentary hailing the tremendous
contributions Deng Xiaoping's theory has made in building
socialism in China.
</P>
<P>
The following are excerpts from the commentary:
</P>
<P>
The 14th Party Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
held in 1992 made a historic decision to establish Deng Xiaoping's
theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics as the
guideline of the whole party and required all party members to
embody the theory.
</P>
<P>
The CPC upholds this great Marxist theoretical banner in
contemporary China.
</P>
<P>
China's reform and opening and its moderization drive have
brought the country into a new era since the 14th Party
Congress. The country's economy in the period has been kept on a
fast track marked by sustained, speedy and sound development, and
the goal to quadruple China's gross domestic product has been
scored ahead of schedule.
</P>
<P>
The past five years has been a brilliant, victorious period for
China.
</P>
<P>
The success is based on the constant efforts of the CPC Central
Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin at the core, to arm and educate
the whole party, cadres and the Chinese people with Deng's theory,
now the spiritual pillar of the people of all ethnic groups in
China.
</P>
<P>
The success should also be attributed to the creative work done
by the CPC Central Committee in the implementation of a series of
strategic measures meant to solve certain critical problems and
unify the people of all ethnic groups.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
