<HEADLINE> Zambian President to Visit Indonesia Tomorrow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Zambian President Frederick
Jacob Titus Chiluba is expected to arrive here Thursday for talks
with president Soeharto on how to enhance the two countries'
bilateral economic cooperation, a senior official said.
</P>
<P>
'President Chiluba's upcoming three-day visit is mainly aimed
at seeking opportunities to strengthen Zambia's economic and trade
relations with Indonesia,' Minister/State Secretary Moerdiono said
here today.
</P>
<P>
There are many opportunities the two countries could explore to
increase their bilateral trade, Moerdiono said, adding that the
people of Zambia as well as other African countries are already
familiar with some Indonesian-made products such as garments,
electronics and footwear.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia on the other hand imports copper, leather, tobacco
and metal goods from Zambia, he added.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba is scheduled to hold a tete-a-tete with Soeharto on
Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
The Zambian president and his entourage will leave Jakarta on
Sunday for Singapore.  
</P>
