<HEADLINE> Armenia, China to Further Boost Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YEREVAN, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Armenian President Levon
Ter-Petrocyan told visiting senior Chinese legislator Wang
Bingqian that Armenia wishes to expand cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
The president, praising China's role in international affairs,
pointed out that there are many prospects for the development of
good relations between his country and China.
</P>
<P>
Wang, vice-chairman of the Chinese National People's Congress
(NPC) Standing Committee, said China is pleased with the cordial
development of Sino-Armenian relations since the two countries
established diplomatic relations five years ago.
</P>
<P>
China will continue to encourage cooperation with Armenia in
various fields, said Wang, who headed a NPC delegation to Armenia
Monday on a goodwill visit.
</P>
<P>
China would like to see peace and stability come to the
Transcaucasian region, which covers Armenia, Georgia and
Azerbaijan, Wang added.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will leave Armenia Thursday for a 10-day
goodwill visit to the other two Transcaucasian countries. 
</P>
