<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 40 Teams to Climb 19 Peaks of Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 20 (Xinhua) -- A total of 40 expedition teams
has got permission to climb 19 different peaks of Nepal in the
coming autumn season which runs from September 1 to November 15.
</P>
<P>
Of the 40 teams, two from France and Mexico respectively have
been given permission to climb the 8,848-metre-high Mt.
Qomolangma, the highest peak of the world, said a press release
issued today by Nepali Ministry of Tourism and Civil Aviation.
</P>
<P>
The rest target peaks include four above 6,500 meters, nine
above 7,100 meters and five over 8,000 meters, the release said.
</P>
<P>
The 40 expedition teams, which have a total of 289 members,
come from Japan, Italy, Germany, Netherlands, Austria, the United
States, Switzerland, Spain, Ukraine, Slovak, Slovene, Denmark, the
Czech Republic, Britain, France, Australia and Mexico.
</P>
<P>
Forty-eight expeditions were permitted to climb peaks of Nepal
during the spring season which lasted from March 1 to May 31.
</P>
<P>
And 47 climbers scaled Mt. Qomolangma during the spring season.
</P>
<P>
Seven mountaineers lost their lives during this season.
</P>
