<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Recovered As U.S. Bourse Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Further recovery on Wall Street
overnight and bargain hunting helped winch the Australian bourse
higher today, however, trading was largely uninspired as investors
remained unconvinced the US slide was over.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index posted a modest gain of 9.8 points to
end at 2,630.7.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index added 10.7 points to 4,232.5, while
the all resources index rose 9.7 to 1,381.8 points.
</P>
<P>
News Crop shares slipped 10 cents, but its preferred shares
climbed seven to 4.87 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Among other industrial leaders, Coca Cola gained 15 cents, Lend
Lease Jumped 35 to 29.65 Australian dollars, Brambles strengthened
20 cents and Mayne Nickless edged up 11 to 8.32 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
