creation of permanent public jobs" for the country's youth as
planned by the Socialist government of Prime Minister Lionel
Jospin.
</P>
<P>
In a brief statement published by the French presidential
office, Chirac, who returned recently to Paris from a vacation,
said that he is counting on private enterprises to create jobs to
reduce France's 12.8 percent unemployment rate.
</P>
<P>
"It is jobs in the private sector which will reduce the
unemployment," Chirac said, adding that the forthcoming national
job conference in France will discuss the creation of jobs by
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Minister of Employment and Solidarity Martine
Aubry will present to the council of ministers today a draft law
creating 350,000 jobs in the public sector within three years,
which is expected to cost the state 35 billion francs (5.8 billion
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
This is partial fulfilment of the electoral promises made by
the Socialist Party during legislative elections in May and June,
which brought a Left-wing coalition to power in France. 
