Athens, Rome, Buenos Aires and Stockholm have also bid for the
2004 Olympic games.
</P>
<P>
According to the Pretoria statement, South Africa and
Switzerland have enjoyed excellent relations for several decades.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland is one of South Africa's main economic partners.
Direct foreign investment from the country has grown steadily,
particularly since 1994, which witnessed the first all-race
elections in South Africa, with the value of new investments
approaching 213 million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland reportedly has contributed to South Africa close
to 63.82 million U.S. Dollars for the reconstruction and
development program since 1994.
</P>
<P>
