<BODY>
<HEADLINE> House Fire Kills Seven in Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 20 (Xinhua) -- An overnight house fire in the
northern German town of Rheine killed seven people, including four
children, and seriously injured two others, the local media
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The deaths were likely to be all members of an ethnic-German
family which migrated to Germany from the former Soviet Union five
years ago, police said.
</P>
<P>
The two injured had eventually managed to escape the fire by
jumping from a second-floor window to a mattress which
firefighters had dragged before the house from a nearby bed shop.
</P>
<P>
Although the fire had been put out, the cause was not
immediately known. Preliminary investigations by local
authorities pointed to a family tragedy caused by panic reaction
after a quarrel on Tuesday evening. 
</P>
</TEXT>
