<DOCNO> XIE19970820.0162 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambican Landmine-clearing Delegation Visits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- A Mozambican delegation of the
National Landmines Clearing Committee led by its President Osorio
Severino, arrived in Luanda Tuesday evening for a five-day
working visit to Angola.
</P>
<P>
In a speech to the press at the airport, Severino said, the
main aim of the Mozambican delegation is to exchanges with Angola
their experiences in landmine clearing.
</P>
<P>
Regarding Mozambique's progress in removing landmines,
Severino said, the urgent period for landmine clearing has come
to an end. At the moment, the major issue for landmine removing
is to consolidate the peace process and promote economic
development.
</P>
<P>
According to him, landmine clearing has opened the gate for the
realization of national economy and social development.
</P>
<P>
During their stay in Angola, the Mozambican delegation will
visit the School of Landmine Clearing located on the outskirts of
Luanda.
</P>
<P>
They will also visit Kuito, the city with the most landmines,
to acquaint themselves with its progress in landmine clearing.
</P>
<P>
Angola and Mozambique were both suffering from long-time civil
war, during which a large number of landmines were planted,
making them the countries with the most landmines in the African
continent.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the International Red Cross, there are 15
million landmines in Angola as against the 3 million in
Mozambique. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
