<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Legislative Council Bill Tabled for Debate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) government today tabled the
Legislative Council Bill to a Provisional Legislative Council
meeting for the first and second readings.
</P>
<P>
The bill, drafted by the SAR government, provides overall
arrangements and legal basis for the first SAR Legislative Council
elections due to taking place in May next year.
</P>
<P>
According to the bill, the Legislative Council of the Hong Kong
SAR will be composed of 60 members, with 30 to be returned by 30
functional constituencies, 10 by the Election Committee and 20
through direct elections in five geographical constituencies.
</P>
<P>
When tabling the bill to the Council, Secretary for Electoral
Affairs Michael Suen Ming-yeung said that the clear and consistent
objective of the SAR government is to ensure that elections take
place on an open, fair and honest basis, so that all candidates
can compete on a level playing field.  
