<HEADLINE> 70 People Die Of Malaria in S. African Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 20 (Xinhua) -- At least 70 people have
died after contracting the deadly tropical disease malaria in
South Africa's Northern Province during the 1996/97 period,
sources reaching here said today.
</P>
<P>
Philip Kruger, Malaria Co-Ordinator, said more than 6,260
people contracted the disease during this period, which was the
worst malaria season for the province in many years.
</P>
<P>
During the 1995/96 season, 34 people died of the disease in
3,510 reported cases.
</P>
<P>
Kruger said the good rainy season for the past two years was
the most significant contributor to malaria reaching epidemic
proportions.
</P>
<P>
"Should predictions be true that the phenomenon of El Nino was
building up over the ocean, generally associated with dry seasons
and even droughts, we can again expect a high incidence of
malaria (in the northern province)," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
