<HEADLINE> German Aid for Chongqing Ecology Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The German government plans to
provide 12 million German marks in gratis assistance to help
southwest China's Chongqing protect and construct forests.
</P>
<P>
A group of German experts is currently visiting the city to
investigate and prepare for an extensive ecological project which
will include planting trees on 35,000 hectares in several
poverty-stricken counties.
</P>
<P>
Experts say the project will also help to curb soil erosion and
raise the income level of farmers in the region.
</P>
<P>
