<HEADLINE> Shanghai To Enhance Supervision Over Insurance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China
(PBOC), the nation's central bank, is preparing to adopt measures
to enhance supervision over Shanghai's insurance market.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, one of the two Chinese cities permitting overseas
insurance companies to engage in local businesses, is also home to
the nation's largest insurance market.
</P>
<P>
Related measures will be announced before the end of this
month, according to the local branch of the central bank.
</P>
<P>
The bank will require all insurance companies in the city to
establish risk control and internal auditing systems.
</P>
<P>
"In principle, no insurer will be permitted to open new
branches in the second half of this year, and the clauses in and
premium rates for insurance policies which contradict central bank
rules will be nullified," according to bank officials.
</P>
<P>
The bank will try to rectify the order of the local insurance
market, and reduce the bad assets of insurance companies. 
</P>
