<HEADLINE> Namibian Deputy Prime Minister Arrives in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Namibian Deputy Prime Minister
Hendrik Witbooi arrived here this afternoon for a weekly official
visit to China as guest of the Chinese Government.
</P>
<P>
Accompanying Witbooi are Mrs. Paulina Witbooi, Minister of
Regional, Local Government and Housing Nicky Iyambo and other
Namibian cabinet officials.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Assistant Foreign Minister Ji Peiding met Witbooi at
the airport.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Prime Minister Witbooi will also travel to central
China's Henan Province and east China's Shanghai municipality
besides Beijing.  
