<HEADLINE> PLA General Meets US Deputy Under-Secretary of Defense </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- A senior People's Liberation
Army (PLA) official said today that Sino-US relations will develop
in a healthy and steady way if the two countries work together to
make it happen.
</P>
<P>
General Wang Ke, member of the Central Military Commission,
said in a meeting here today with a US logistics delegation, led
by Deputy Under-Secretary of Defense Paul J. Hoeper, that the
relationship between the two armed forces is an important aspect
of the overall bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Recent years have witnessed an increase of high-level exchanges
of visits between the two armed forces, Wand noted, adding that
there is new progress in the cooperation involving logistics.
</P>
<P>
Wang, who is also director of the PLA General Logistics
Department, said he is convinced that Hoeper's visit will have a
positive influence on the improvement of cooperation in logistics
and the understanding and friendship between the two armed forces.
</P>
<P>
China and the US are two important countries in the world, Wang
noted, stressing that the Chinese government puts high value on
Sino-US relations and has made non-stop efforts to develop
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Wang also briefed the guests on China's economic construction,
the logistics building of the PLA, as well as China's defense
policy.
</P>
<P>
Hoeper said that the delegation is composed of specialized
personnel in all fields, adding that they are interested in what
they have seen concerning the PLA's logistics facilities.
</P>
<P>
Hoeper continued that the delegation has had important and
candid talks with their hosts, emphasizing that aim of the
delegation's visit is to deepen the level of trust between the two
countries and their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Wen Guangchun, deputy director of PLA General Logistics
Department, attended the meeting. Wen held talks with Hoeper on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Hoeper and his party arrived here on August 16 as guests of PLA
General Logistics Department.
</P>
<P>
 
</P>
</TEXT>
