<HEADLINE> Advanced AN-140 Plane Ready for Maiden Flights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The prototype of the advanced
AN-140 passenger plane has nearly finished all ground trials and
is ready for its maiden flights, press here reported today.
</P>
<P>
Antonov Aviation Design &AMP; Production Complex, the manufacturing
company, said the plane was assembled in June, and has been
undergoing a series of ground trials limited to its performance on
runways and taxiways.
</P>
<P>
AN-140, capable of carrying 52 passengers and using airfields
with rather rough runways, is supposed to replace AN-24s and
YAK-40s which served mostly on domestic flights in the member
countries of the Commonwealth of Independent States.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that AN-140 will be highly competitive on markets,
because of its superb passenger comfort and safety standard and
low fuel consumption which will be less than half of that of AN-24.
</P>
<P>
Its serial production will be centered in Ukraine's second
largest city, Kharkov and Russia's Samara. A plant in Isfahan,
Iran, will likely be the third manufacturing center for AN-140s.
</P>
<P>
The company indicated that AN-140 will appear on global markets
as early as 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
