<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Opera on Three Gorges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The first Western-style opera
about the Three Gorges on the Yangtze River, a famous tourist site
and future home of the world's largest dam, will be staged later
this month in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The opera, entitled "The Goddess of the Gorges," highlights an
ancient legend about a female celestial who fell in love with a
sailor plying the waters of the Three Gorges. Natural and social
factors combine to destroy their love affair. The couple commits
suicide and the female celestial is transformed into a mountain
peak on the banks of the Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
Chinese people over the centuries have written thousands of
poems and pieces of prose to memorialize the couple and the
mountain. The mountain known as the "Goddess" has long been a
major attraction in the Three Gorges.
</P>
<P>
The opera, produced by the Chongqing Opera Troupe, will be
presented as part of festivities scheduled for the '97 China
International Opera and Dance Year. The opera is expected to
provide foreign tourists with a new image of the Three Gorges.
</P>
<P>
The artists from Chongqing, the largest commercial city in
southwest China, view the opera as a tribute to the massive
reservoir which will be completed along the Yangtze later this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
