<HEADLINE> Food Hygiene Standard to Be Established in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 20 (Xinhua) --The Kampala City Council (KCC)
is hammering out a code governing the hygiene standard in food
processing, according to ''The Monitor'' today.
</P>
<P>
Simon Kuhumuza, the KCC Public Relations Officer, told the
paper that it will be compulsory for bucheries, hotels and
take-aways to follow the code on food.
</P>
<P>
