<HEADLINE> Shanghai Art Work Auction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Dekang Auction
Co. recorded a total transaction volume of 3.87 million yuan
(433,750 US dollars) for an art auction held between Aug. 10-17.
</P>
<P>
The auction, which offered more than 1,200 works of art and
recorded a transaction volume of 77.7 percent, attracted
collectors from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan, as well as from a
number of other countries and regions, including Singapore.
</P>
<P>
According to Dekang Deputy-Manager Qian Jiansheng, about 20
percent of the buyers were ordinary citizens from Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The company attempted to lure buyers by offering 200 works with
no minimum prices. Said works were sold at prices ranging between
500 yuan (62 US dollars) and 3,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
"The auction provided a good way to increase my knowledge of
collecting and gain the latest market information," according to
one man named Liu, a worker with a mediocre income and one of
10,000 collectors in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Qian noted that an increasing number of people consider
auctions to be a good thing to engage in low risk
investment. Ten-odd Shanghai auction companies specializing in art
works note the vast potential for the local market.
</P>
<P>
Dekang, founded in 1992, caters to the tastes of ordinary
citizens and has held nearly 90 weekend mini-auctions since
1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
