<HEADLINE> White-Collar Workers Promote Pudong Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Pudong, the famous economic
development zone in Shanghai, China's largest city, is attracting
more senior foreign management and technical personnel, as well as
an increasing volume of foreign capital.
</P>
<P>
According to an official from Pudong Customs, related offices
have completed entrance registration procedures for 624 senior
management and technical personnel and their families since 1995,
with the new arrivals scheduled for long-term work in Pudong's
foreign-funded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Most work for well-known enterprises from Japan, Hong Kong and
the United States, including Sony, Kodak, Fuji and General Motors.
</P>
<P>
In addition, senior financial managers are working in the
growing number of foreign-funded banks in Pudong.
</P>
<P>
Pudong Customs has also completed departure registration
procedures for 45 foreigners returning home after fulfilling their
assignment to established enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Authoritative sources from Pudong's economic and trade sector
point out that the shift in foreigners arriving in the zone
indicates that foreign-funded enterprises have entered normal
operational stages.
</P>
<P>
Pudong had 4,667 foreign-funded projects by the end of June,
with total contracted investments standing at 23.07 billion US
dollars. Pudong ranks first in the nation with a 90 percent
allocation rate for contracted investments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
