<DOCNO> XIE19970820.0216 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guilin-Beihai Expressway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Construction of an expressway
linking the scenic city of Guilin with the port city of Beihai is
proceeding smoothly.
</P>
<P>
The northern section linking Guilin and Liuzhou has opened to
traffic and the Qinzhou-Fangchenggang section to the south is
scheduled to open in October. Construction of two other sections
is also in full swing.
</P>
<P>
The 580 km expressway, the longest highway currently under
construction in the country, is considered vital to the Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region. The expressway will not only link the
two most important local cities, but also will be linked to
high-grade roads in neighboring Guizhou and Hunan provinces to the
north, and Zanjiang City in Guangdong Province to the south. The
completed expressway will be a major trunk line linking southwest
China to the sea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
