<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov Upset at Hamlet Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New York, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Yevgeny Kafelnikov, Sunday's
winner of the Pilot Pen tournament, was on Tuesday bounced out of
the Hamlet Cup in the opening round.
</P>
<P>
The third-seeded Russian, two days after being crowned champion
in New Haven, was ousted by Frenchman Arnaud Boetsch 6-4, 7-6
(8-6).
</P>
<P>
Second seed Goran Ivanisevic of Croatia took one hour and 18
minutes to beat Ramon Delgado of Paraguay 7-5, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday's actions also saw double Australian victories when
Todd Woodbridge beat Brazilian Jaime Ocins 6-3, 6-4 and Patrick
Rafter overcame Slovakian Karol Kucera 6-3, 3-6, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
A third Aussie, Mark Woodforde, lost to Marc-Kevin Goellner of
Germany 3-6, 6-4, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Seventh-seeded Petr Korda withdrew from the Hamlet after
injuring his left ankle during a practice session, and was not
sure he would be ready for the U.S. Open.
</P>
<P>
Korda was replaced in the draw by Spaniard Carlos Costa, who
lost to Sweden's Jonas Bjorkman 6-2, 6-0. 
</P>
</TEXT>
