<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Sell State Utility Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzanian government
is making plans for privatizing and restructuring four state
giant utility companies by June 1999.
</P>
<P>
The companies due to be privatized are the Tanzania Harbors
Authority, the Tanzania Electric Supply Co. Ltd., the Dar es
Salaam Water and Sewage Authority and the Tanzania
Telecommunications Co. Ltd..
</P>
<P>
The scheme was made public at the on-going National Assembly
session by Nassoro Malocho, Minister of State in the President's
Office, the local press today quoted him as saying.
</P>
<P>
Restructuring has already started for the giant utility firms,
which will be completed with privatization, Malocho told the
National Assembly.
</P>
<P>
The Parastatal Sector Reform Commission (PSRC) of Tanzania is
responsible for fulfilling the plans.
</P>
<P>
PSRC spent most of 1996/97 making privatization plans for the
major utility firms, according to Malocho.
</P>
<P>
PSRC, the institution in charge of reform of parastatals,
started operation during the 1992/93 financial year. It has
already brought about 79 state firms to restructuring, through
the sale of shares to different investor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
