<HEADLINE> Inflation Decreases in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's annual inflation rate
in July decreased to 9.6 percent from 10.1 percent in June,
reported the local daily "The New Vision" today.
</P>
<P>
A report issued recently by the state-owned Bank of Uganda was
quoted as saying that this is a result of falling in food prices
after the April-May raining season.
</P>
<P>
Another reason is that the Bank of Uganda increased its public
borrowing through treasury bills from 24.5 billion shillings
(about 24.5 million U.S. Dollars) in June to 37.7 billion
shilling in July, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
