<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
gained ground today after another solid rise on Wall Street
overnight.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 9 points higher at 2,503 with a turnover
of 71 million NZ dollars (45 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The news of the day was the profit results from Fletcher
Challenger. Net profit last year for the group fell nearly 8
percent, but was within the expectation of brokers. The profit was
mainly dragged down by a 50 million-dollar (32 million US dollars)
loss in Fletcher Paper, largely because of poor world prices and a
400 million-dollar (256 million US dollars) write-down on the
value of a UK subsidiary. However, Fletcher Paper shares still
climbed 12 cents to 342 cents.
</P>
<P>
Other leaders were mixed. Telecom shares dropped 2c to 758c.
Brierley Investment gained 1c to 139c. Carter Holt Harvey, Air New
Zealand and Lion Nathan all stayed unchanged at 350c, 298c and
400c respectively.  
</P>
