<HEADLINE> Tax Collection Objective Fulfilled in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 20 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzania Revenue
Authority (TRA) collected a total of 523.7 billion shillings
(872.8 million US Dollars) in taxes, close to 98 percent of its
objective, Finance Minister Daniel Yoha told the National
Assembly on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
About 626.7 billion shillings (about one billion U.S.Dollars)
in tax revenue has been planned for this fiscal year, Yoha said.
</P>
<P>
The TRA has carried out extensive studies on the operational
problems of the customs department with a view to finding an
appropriate way to restructure its activities, the minister
added.
</P>
<P>
Yoha said that the finance department will now be operating on
a computerized basis as well as adopting the single bill of entry
to increase efficiency.
</P>
<P>
As for the sales tax department, Yoha said, the TRA is making
preparations for the introduction of the Value Added Tax (VAT)
system to be operational by July 1, 1998. 
</P>
