<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Long March 3B Rocket </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 20 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese-produced Long March 3B
rocket successfully lifted-off from the Xichang Launch Center in
southwest China's Sichuan Province early this morning carrying a
telecommunications satellite belonging to the Mabuhay Philippines
Satellite Corp.
</P>
<P>
The three-stage Long March 3B, developed by the Chinese Academy
of Carrier Rocket Technology, is now the country's most powerful
satellite launch vehicle. The new rocket can place a 5,000-kg
payload into geosynchronous orbit with a 28.5 degree angle of
obliquity.
</P>
<P>
The 3B model, which is 54.838 meters long and has a lift-off
propulsion of 426 tons, integrates all proven and flight-tested
technology of the Long March rocket family and offers excellent
continuity and reliability.
</P>
<P>
The main stage of the Long March 3B rocket, which includes all
features of the Long March 3A carrier rocket, is also equipped
with a larger fuel tank, an improved overall structure and bigger
fairing, and the application of more highly sophisticated
technology.
</P>
<P>
The first stage of the new Long March 3B rocket has an
additional four propulsion units similar to those on the Long
March II model. Flight control and remote sensing systems on the
new model were modified on the basis of the Long March 3A
rocket. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
