<HEADLINE> Russian Premier Vows to Catch Murderer of Deputy Mayor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin pledged today that the murderer of a deputy mayor
would not be allowed to remain at large.
</P>
<P>
Mikhail Manevich, 36, deputy mayor and chairman of the State
Property Committee of St. Petersburg, was attacked early Monday on
his way to work. He died later.
</P>
<P>
The attack against such a senior civil servant was shocking,
said Chernomyrdin, who is heading a team investigating the
assassination.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, President Boris Yeltsin ordered the Federal Security
Service, the Interior Ministry, the General Procuratorate and
other departments to take necessary measures as soon as possible
to investigate the case. 
</P>
