<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment Increases in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 20 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investment in Myanmar
reached 6.361 billion U.S. dollars at the end of July this year,
the official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
The investment raised for 270 permitted projects came from 22
countries and regions, the report said, quoting the latest
official statistics.
</P>
<P>
In the first seven months of this year, foreign investment
increased four times over the corresponding period of last year
while domestic investment increased eight times, the report said.
But it did not give specific figures.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting on promoting foreign and domestic investment here
Tuesday, Brigadier General Maung Maung, secretary of the Myanmar
Investment Commission (MIC), called for concerted efforts to
attract more foreign investment this year by granting generous
exemption or tax holiday and land use.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar's Foreign Investment Law and Citizens Investment Law,
promulgated in November 1988 and April 1994 respectively, provide
for investment incentives in terms of tariffs and taxes.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has been transferring to a market-oriented economy from
a central economy since late 1988, when it opened its doors to the
outside world.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was attended by officials of 15 Myanmar ministries.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
