<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Colombian Nobel
Laureate Gabriel Garcia Marquez condemned today the Colombian
government for misusing influence in the country's public auction
of frequency modulated radio stations.
</P>
<P>
In a statement to radio RCN, the winner of the 1982 Nobel Prize
for Literature warned that the government may do the same with
television.
</P>
<P>
