Communications Minister Arboleda Gomez have reportedly signed an
agreement to sell the 40 radio stations, currently for public
bidding, to "President Ernesto Samper`s friends".
</P>
<P>
Garcia Marquez has said he would support his partners at the
news TV show "Gap" to bid for a TV station, expected to be on
auction on January 1, 1998, though he knows they have little
chance due to their outspoken opposition to the president.
</P>
<P>
"Gap" is known for its critical comments on the
government. 
