<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Ireland's triple Olympic champion
Michelle de Bruin took her first gold medal in women's 400 meters
individual medley at the European Swimming Championships in
Seville, Spain on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
De Bruin, now uses her married name instead of Michelle Smith
at the Atlanta Game.
</P>
<P>
She was challenged by European junior champion Yana Klochkova
in the 400 meters individual medley with a time of four minutes
42.08 seconds, almost three seconds slower than her 4:39.18 in
1996 Atlanta, and showed her prowess on the last length.
</P>
<P>
She earned her first two European titles at the last
championships in Vienna in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Olympic silver medallist Sandra Voelker of German won the
women's 100 meters freestyle title with 55.38 and give Germany the
first pool swimming title of the 12-day championships.
</P>
<P>
Alexander Goukov of Belarus won the men's 100 meters
breaststroke, edging 1988 Olympic silver medallist Karoly Guttler
of Hungary into second place by 0.06 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Britain's Paul Palmer, silver medallist at the 1995 European
championships in the 200 freestyle, won the event in 1:48.85, with
Rosolino second at 1:49.02. 
