<HEADLINE> Ireland's Olympic Champion Faces Punishment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Ireland's triple Olympic champion
Michelle de Bruin stirred up trouble with officials after winning
women's 400 meters individual medley in Seville, Spain on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
De Bruin, now using her married name instead of Michelle Smith
at the Atlanta Olympics, risked the ultimate punishment of
disqualification from the championships for missing the mandatory
post-race press conference, European Swimming League president
Bartolo Consolo said.
</P>
<P>
After a few brief comments to Irish television, De Bruin went
directly to doping test and then left the pool.
</P>
<P>
Rules regarding European championship medallists attending
press conferences were introduced after the 1995 championships in
Vienna when German Franziska van Almsick unconcerned the media.
</P>
<P>
The European Swimming League bureau is due to meet on Wednesday
morning to make a decision.  
</P>
