<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0000 GMT, August 20 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO -- The Arab League (AL) has warned the Walt Disney Film
Production Company and its affiliates against churning out films
that mar the image of Arabs and Muslims, the Egyptian MENA news
agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
AL Assistant Secretary General Saeed Kamal said that
Washington-based U.S.-Arab Committee on Combating Racial
Segregation had previously warned the company against producing
such films. (Egypt-AL-Walt Disney)
</P>
<P>
LAGOS -- The West African Peace-keeping Force known as ECOMOG
is to adjust its deployment in Liberia to ensure the national
security of that country.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here Tuesday quoted ECOMOG commander,
major-general Victor Malu as saying this at the weekend at the
ECOMOG headquarters in Monrovia, during a visit by Kalu Kaluniya,
the out-going U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees' resident
representative in Liberia.
</P>
<P>
The commander said that the re-deployment will fortify
Liberia's border with its neighboring countries, especially with
Sierra Leone. (Liberia-deployment)
</P>
<P>
DAMASCUS -- Syria and Lebanon on Tuesday condemned Israeli
brutal shelling of civilian targets in the southern Lebanese city
of Sidon, killing at least nine and wounding many others.
</P>
<P>
The condemnation was made in the minutes signed by Syrian Prime
Minister Mahmoud Zobie and his Lebanese counterpart Rafiq Hariri
after their talks here. (Syria-Lebanon-condemnation)
</P>
<P>
BONN -- The German government and a Jewish group opened a
two-day talks Tuesday on compensation to Holocaust survivors now
living in the former East Bloc.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday's talks were held in the German Finance Ministry and
were described as preliminary prior to the Wednesday meeting
between German Chancellor Helmut Kohl's chief of staff, Friedrich
Bohl, and representatives of the Jewish Claims Conference.
(Germany-Holocaust Survivors)
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak has ordered a
transfer of 10 million U.S. dollars at once to the Palestinian
National Authority (PNA) which is suffering from a financial
freeze imposed by Israel, Egypt's MENA news agency said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
During a telephone contact Tuesday, Mubarak informed PNA
President Yasser Arafat that he is making efforts to ease the
financial crisis through which the Palestinian government and its
people are passing through. (Egypt-PNA-Money Transfer)
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The world population was estimated at 5.751
billion in mid-1996, 0.61 percent more than the mid-year estimates
in 1995, the UN Statistics Division reported here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The latest statistics show that the 10 most-populous countries
each with over 100 million people have a combined population of
3.44 billion while people of the 13 countries, each with a
population between 50 and 100 million, number 834 million. The
population of the 23 countries in the two groups above amounts to
4.249 billion, nearly three quarters of the world total.
(UN-Population) 
</P>
</TEXT>
