<HEADLINE> Germans Take Synchronised Diving Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 19 (Xinhua) -- German pair Holger Schlepps and
Alexander Mesch took the title of the men's 3-meter springboard
synchronised diving at the European swimming championships in
Seville, Spain on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Schlepps and Mesch finished 284.34 points edging Jose Luis
Hidalgo and Ruben Santos of Spain, who collected 283.92 points.
</P>
<P>
Nicola Marconi and Donald Miranda came to the third 277.38
points. 
</P>
