<HEADLINE> Costa Rica Appoints New Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rica named Spaniard Juan
Luis Hernandez as their new national soccer coach on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Hernandez, currently in charge of first division Cartagines,
became the team's third coach this year following the dismissal of
Argentina's Horacio Cordero.
</P>
<P>
Cordero was sacked last Thursday in the wake of a 0-0 home draw
with El Salvador in a World Cup qualifier. 
</P>
