<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Milan Warms up by Defeating Juventus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 19 (Xinhua) -- AC Milan warmed up for the upcoming
new season by defeating the Italian champions Juventus 3-1 in a
highly competitive pre-season friendly held at Milan on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Juventus was leading 1-0 at the end of the first half thanks to
a header from Antonio Conte in the 30th minute.
</P>
<P>
But Milan roared back in the second half with three goals in a
stunning eight minute assault on the Juventus defence.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's Andre Cruz opened the scoring in the 54th minute and
six minutes later Milan's new Dutch signing, Patrick Kluivert,
made it 2-1 with a close range blow.
</P>
<P>
Milan's win was sealed in the 62nd minute by Liberian George
Weah, who broke free in the area to slot the ball behind the
Juventus keeper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
